# Maps & Navigation

A collection of the best mapping and navigation platforms focused on privacy, offline access, open-source data, and freedom from centralized ecosystems.

---

# Organic Maps

- Website: https://organicmaps.app
- Open Source: Yes
- Privacy Focused: Extremely

## Why Use It?

Organic Maps is a lightweight offline maps app focused on privacy and simplicity.

### Unique Benefits

- Fully offline maps
- No tracking or ads
- OpenStreetMap powered
- Fast and lightweight
- Battery efficient

### Best For

Travelers and users wanting private offline navigation.

---

# OpenStreetMap

- Website: https://www.openstreetmap.org
- Open Source: Yes
- Privacy Focused: Yes

## Why Use It?

OpenStreetMap is a community-driven map database used by many privacy-focused apps and services.

### Unique Benefits

- Community maintained
- Open geographic data
- Free to use
- Frequently updated
- Used by many alternative map apps

### Best For

Developers and users supporting open map infrastructure.

---

# OsmAnd

- Website: https://osmand.net
- Open Source: Yes
- Privacy Focused: Extremely

## Why Use It?

OsmAnd is a feature-rich offline navigation app built on OpenStreetMap data.

### Unique Benefits

- Offline navigation
- Advanced route customization
- Hiking and cycling maps
- Terrain and contour support
- Voice navigation

### Best For

Hikers, cyclists, and advanced navigation users.

---

# Magic Earth

- Website: https://www.magicearth.com
- Open Source: No
- Privacy Focused: Yes

## Why Use It?

Magic Earth combines strong privacy protections with a polished modern navigation experience.

### Unique Benefits

- No tracking
- Dashcam support
- Traffic and navigation features
- OpenStreetMap powered
- Clean interface

### Best For

Users wanting a Google Maps replacement with a polished UI.

